cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a deep convolutional neural network (CNN) for object detection, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of semantic segmentation-aware features suggests a focus on learning high-level representations, which is also relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The iterative localization mechanism involves regression models, which are commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on the PASCAL VOC dataset, which is a benchmark commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
